Question: What type of cultural arts or entertainment opportunities would you like to see more of in Austin?

Response ID: resp_2241
Response Text: 1. Opportunities that improve the ability for artists to live and do their creative work in Austin. One example is the Artist Resource Grants that North Adams, MA did - https://www.assetsforartists.org/blog/2020/4/9/north-adams-artist-resource-grants.
2. Continued and expanded support for cultural activities that serve niche communities, and for the venues that host them.
3. More rigorous support for critical, mid-level, artist-run institutions in Austin that are at risk due to federal funding cancellation and state funding precarity. Austinites have long benefited from the unique cultural environment that orgs in this tier foster. The city will need to set up to support them through this period of funding crisis because private philanthropy is not here like it is in Houston or Dallas (especially for the smaller-budget orgs serving and platforming the creatives of Austin).
4. Cultural export - resources for Austin-based artists to show their work elsewhere.

